# Local Plugin Execution

- NoC work runs locally in the approved workspace.
- Do not use Omnistation as an execution workspace for NoC.
- Remote hosts may be used for non-critical research only.
- Base, plugin and notary-workstation minimum requirements are defined in [docs/de/minimum-requirements.md](../../docs/de/minimum-requirements.md) and [docs/en/minimum-requirements.md](../../docs/en/minimum-requirements.md).
- Run `python scripts/startup_check.py --profile plugin-dev --ide auto` before plugin development.
- Run `python scripts/startup_check.py --profile notary-workstation --ide auto` before card-reader, morris or XNP-adjacent tests.
- Plugin and connector plans are documented under [docs/de/plugin-plans/](../../docs/de/plugin-plans) and [docs/en/plugin-plans/](../../docs/en/plugin-plans).
- Plans must distinguish:
  - proposed intent,
  - plan preview,
  - human review,
  - reconciler execution,
  - audit evidence,
  - Day2 drift handling.
- No secrets, API keys, browser callback tokens, or local credentials may be stored in the repository.
